                <p>THQ Nordic and Bugbear Entertainment have confirmed that <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/games/wreckfest-2/" data-ref-id="5000-638027">Wreckfest 2</a>, a sequel to their wildly destructive racing game, will finally enter early access on March 20. We also have a solid idea of what Wreckfest 2 will feature when it enters early access and what will be added over time.</p><p>The original <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/games/wreckfest/" data-ref-id="5000-171651">Wreckfest</a> was one of the first early-access success stories. It stood out due to its penchant for destruction with impressive damage models that let its vehicles get significantly more busted and bruised than your typical racer. Now, over a decade after Wreckfest's early access release, Bugbear and THQ Nordic are going through the same process with its sequel, which ups the ante with a rebuilt physics engine that makes the damage simulation for its cars even more detailed.</p>



    
