      </div>
<p>The early-access trailer demonstrates the destructive nature of Wreckfest 2's gameplay, as we see racers bump and crash into each other while speeding through a junkyard. This is presumably from one of the three modes that will be available in Wreckfest 2 at release: Racing, Derby, and Multiplayer. Bugbear Entertainment has teased what it plans to add to its racer over time, and it goes beyond just adding more tracks and car-customization options.</p><p>During early access, Wreckfest 2 will receive a reworked career mode that will tailor itself to how you play Wreckfest 2. The game will also get Challenges, smaller high-score scenarios where players will take control of "unconventional vehicles," and Tournaments. Mod support, skill-based matchmaking, server queues, and the ability to share vehicle designs with other players will also come to Wreckfest 2 during its early-access phase.</p><p>Wreckfest 2 launches on PC via <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/1203190/Wreckfest_2/" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Steam Early Access</a> on March 20; eventually, it will be released on PS5 and Xbox Series X|S as well.</p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
